-- Nigeria foreign reserves fall to five-month low of $37.2 bln
-- By Oludare Mayowa
-- Tue Nov 25, 2014 06:24AM EST
-- None



LAGOS, Nov 25 (Reuters) - Nigeria's foreign reserves fell to a five-month low of $37.17 billion by Nov. 21, down 5.1 percent from the previous month as the central bank stepped up its defence of the ailing naira <NGN=D1> currency, figures on the bank's website showed.

The reserves <NGFXR=ECI> of Africa's biggest economy stood at the same level as at June this year and was at $39.16 billion on Oct. 21, the data showed on Tuesday.